        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>The center includes a study space, market, reception area, boardroom, library, outdoor courtyard and a 159-square-foot “Virtual Duke” interactive screen—the largest of its kind in North Carolina. The administrative building will hold 40 staff members from the Duke Alumni Association and 10 from the Office of Undergraduate Admissions.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Supported by and designed for alumni, the Karsh Center will be a place for current students to connect with graduates. There are more than <a href="https://facts.duke.edu/" target="_blank">170,000</a> active alumni.</p>
<p>“We want students to know early on in their Duke journeys that alumni are there for them—that they are willing to give them advice and help them with their next big steps,” Wilder wrote. “We like to say that the Duke experience isn’t just formed in the years that students are here. It’s forever.”</p>

